Re: Mind control through mass media???
by Vulpine on Tue May 04, 2010 2:59 pm	([msg=38350]see Re: Mind control through mass media???[/msg])
People are stupid. Plain and simple. The only reason mass media holds so much influence over their audience is because people want them to. They want to believe whatever the flashy colors and bright lights tell them. It's easier than doing their homework. They want to believe the political propaganda. It helps them to justify their poorly considered position. To quote Ayn Rand:"The evil of the world is made possible by nothing but the sanction that you give it."Not that you need to collect the Pendants of Courage, Wisdom, and Strength, and then brandish your ancient sword of power in order to fight this... It's really as simple as turning the damn TV off and asking questions.
