by acantho on Thu May 06, 2010 7:14 pm	([msg=38411]see Re: Mind control through mass media???[/msg])
insomaniacal wrote:I feel the same way nowadays. Whenever my girlfriend mentions that new movie with "that" actor, I never have a clue as to what she's talking about. As for mind control, like Goatboy said, most of it's based on subtle hints. Advertisements tend to be much more obvious, but not always. For example, you will never see a villain in any movie/TV show using a Mac. Coincidence? I highly doubt it. Money talks, 'nough said.Product placement !Companies, from apple, to samsung, macdonalds to wendys (see I've been to the US of A before, or maybe just watched Pulp Fiction!), ford to mercedes (think ford specifically made the "cars" for the Judge Dread movie) even the airlines used in movies and shows, the type of guns used etc etc etc and not forgetting the stuff that is not in your face - stuff in the background e.g. a hotel chain in a shot. Companies pay for this exposure and the film companies and TV show makers actively court them for money to use their products/have their products in shot.The strange thing is that the more you are aware that this goes on the more you notice it, but the less you are influenced by it, and those who are less aware of it are more likely to be influenced by it. So yes there is a large amount of subliminal stuff going on, but even more in your face stuff as well.
